                `})}),i.jsxs("p",{children:["This formula works out that if a submission takes twice as long on a certain workload than the best submission then it receives a performance ratio of 2, for example. And"," ",i.jsx(v,{inline:!0,children:"\\(r_{\\bar s, \\bar w} \\geq 1\\)"})," ","for all submissions and workloads. Extending this concept out, a performance profile can then be defined describing the probability on a random workload ",i.jsx(v,{inline:!0,children:"\\(\\bar w\\)"})," ","drawn uniformly from ",i.jsx(v,{inline:!0,children:"\\(W\\)"}),", that"," ",i.jsx(v,{inline:!0,children:"\\(\\bar s\\)"})," will have a performance ratio"," ",i.jsx(v,{inline:!0,children:"\\(r_{\\bar s, \\bar w}\\)"})," of at most ",i.jsx(v,{inline:!0,children:"\\(\\tau\\)"}),"(where ",i.jsx(v,{inline:!0,children:"\\(\\tau \\in [1, \\infty)\\)"}),"):"]}),i.jsx("p",{children:i.jsx(v,{block:!0,dynamic:!0,children:`
